"title":{
"__html":"Hemochromatosis"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"290ad9",
"children":[
"Hemochromatosis"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_hm_s16_1",
"title":{
"__html":"Diagnosis"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"523223",
"children":[
"Diagnosis"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"ee4625",
"children":[
"Hereditary hemochromatosis is an autosomal-recessive disorder characterized by increased intestinal absorption of iron and iron deposition in multiple organs."
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"10c978",
"children":[
"The most common symptoms are erectile dysfunction; fatigue; and ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"osteoarthritis",
"children":[
"OA"
]
},
" involving unusual joints, such as the shoulders, ankles, and elbows."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"524069",
"children":[
"Less commonly, patients may have diabetes, ",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"heart failure",
"children":[
"HF"
]
},
","
]
},
" hyperpigmentation (skin bronzing), and panhypopituitarism."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"0a9699",
"children":[
"Hand radiograph may show distinctive hook-like osteophytes of the second and third ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"metacarpophalangeal",
"children":[
"MCP"
]
},
" joints."
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_hm_s16_2",
"title":{
"__html":"Testing"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"fa6a5a",
"children":[
"Testing"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"42ecdb",
"children":[
"The most appropriate screening tests for hemochromatosis are transferrin saturation and serum ferritin level, with ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"HFE"
]
},
" genotype testing if abnormal."
]
},
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"1",
"contentIds":[
"mk19_bb_hm_f11"
],
"forceOpen":true
},
{
"type":"heading",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
"Don't Be Tricked"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"eab30e",
"children":[
"Advanced liver disease commonly causes an elevated ferritin level, but the iron saturation is usually normal."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"cd5743",
"children":[
"A nondiagnostic ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"HFE"
]
},
" genotype does not rule out a diagnosis of hemochromatosis."
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_hm_s16_3",
"title":{
"__html":"Treatment"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"4c4ac0",
"children":[
"Treatment"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"ef825e",
"children":[
"Patients who are ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"C282Y"
]
},
" homozygous but have normal serum ferritin levels can be monitored without treatment."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"965c86",
"children":[
"Patients with hemochromatosis and an elevated ferritin level should be treated with phlebotomy."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_hm_s16_4",
"title":{
"__html":"Family Screening"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"9420f6",
"children":[
"Family Screening"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"2992be",
"children":[
"First-degree relatives of patients with hemochromatosis should undergo screening."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_hm_s16_5",
"title":{
"__html":"Follow-up Surveillance"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"3af103",
"children":[
"Follow-up Surveillance"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"0e1af7",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"alert",
"children":[
"Screen for ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"hepatocellular carcinoma",
"children":[
"HCC"
]
},
" with ultrasonography every 6 months in patients with cirrhosis."
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_hm_s16_6",
"title":{
"__html":"Test Yourself"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"7866cc",
