"hlId":"a8d652",
"class":"test",
"children":[
"A 68-year-old man has increasing pain in the second and third MCP joints of both hands. Medical history is significant for type 2 diabetes mellitus and HF."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"d160ed",
"class":"test_answer",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Answer:"
]
},
" ",
"For diagnosis, select hemochromatosis. For management, order transferrin saturation and serum ferritin measurement."
]
}
]
}
]
